<docbook><section><title>UsingTheTraceOnIniFileOption</title><para>You can set the &quot;TraceOn&quot; param in the &quot;[Parameters]&quot; section of the  Virtuoso configuration file such that it is enabled on server startup as detailed at:</para><para>	<ulink url="http://docs.openlinksw.com/virtuoso/databaseadmsrv.html#ex_traceoniniopt">http://docs.openlinksw.com/virtuoso/databaseadmsrv.html#ex_traceoniniopt</ulink></para><para> </para><programlisting>[Parameters]
....
TraceOn = soap, errors
...
</programlisting><para> This will enable logging of additional information regarding SOAP calls and SQL run-time errors into the virtuoso.log file.
</para></section></docbook>